data.text:
Hämeenkyrö (Finnish: [ˈhæmeːnˌkyrø]) is a municipality of Finland. It is part of the Pirkanmaa region, and is located 36 kilometres (22 mi) from Tampere. The municipality has a population of 10,300 (30 September 2023) and covers an area of 505.10 square kilometres (195.02 sq mi) of which 41.34 km2 (15.96 sq mi) is water.

Hämeenkyrö is known for its very beautiful landscapes, lakes and berry farms.
